Pretoria - Deputy President Cyril Ramaphosa will on Monday attend and address Eid prayer and celebrations in Lenasia in Gauteng, says the Presidency.The Presidency said the Eid prayer and Celebration is one of the largest assemblies of the Muslim community in South Africa and represents a day of accomplishment after a month of fasting. It is also a day of compassion marked by the compulsory discharge of charity prior to the Eid prayer that is spent on the less fortunate people of our country, the Presidency said. SAnews.gov.zaPretoria Deputy President Cyril Ramaphosa has been presented with a Lifetime Award for Leadership by the Regenesys Business School.Pretoria Deputy President Cyril Ramaphosa says concerted action must be taken to speed up reforms in the agriculture sector so that more marginalised people can be brought into the mainstream economy.Cape Town Work is underway to review the Integrated Plan of Action that was conceptualised to fight gender-based violence.